Pre-Game Insights: Mali and Eswatini will face each other for the first time at the Mbombela Stadium in South Africa.
Eswatini lost their opening game in Group I against Guinea-Bissau with a score of 1-0.
Mali drew their opening game against Mozambique with a score of 1-1.
Mali has qualified for the last nine editions of the AFCON tournament and aims to make it 10 in a row.
Eswatini is ranked 155th in the world, while Mali is ranked 53rd according to the latest FIFA World Rankings.
